A cloud operating model defines how people, processes, and technology work together to manage cloud environments effectively.

Important components include:

* Governance
* Security
* Operations
* Financial management
* DevOps practices
* Compliance
* Service management

For example, an organization may define separate responsibilities for cloud administrators, security engineers, application owners, and finance teams to ensure efficient cloud operations.

A real-life use case is enterprises managing thousands of Azure resources across multiple business units while maintaining accountability and operational efficiency.
